# =======================================================
# Git Commit Message Template
# =======================================================
# Lines starting with '#' are ignored by Git.
# Fill in all sections where applicable.

# 1. TYPE (Required, max 50 chars summary)
# -------------------------------------------------------
# Use one of the conventional commit types:
# feat: new feature
# fix: bug fix
# docs: documentation
# style: formatting / linting / non-functional
# refactor: code change without behavior change
# perf: performance improvement
# test: adding or fixing tests
# chore: build/system/tooling update
# ci: CI/CD changes
# build: build system changes
# revert: reverts a previous commit
# <type>(<scope>): <short summary>

# 2. DESCRIPTION (Optional, wrap at 72 chars)
# -------------------------------------------------------
# Explain *what* was changed and *why* (not how).
# Use bullet points if multiple changes:
# - First change description
# - Second change description
# Reference issues/tickets if applicable:
# Issue: #123
# Jira: PROJECT-456
# <detailed description>

# 3. FOOTER / METADATA (Optional)
# -------------------------------------------------------
# Use for breaking changes, co-authors, or reviewers:
# BREAKING CHANGE: describe the change and impact
# Reviewed-by: <reviewer name>
# Co-authored-by: <name> <email>
# Related-PR: <url>

# =======================================================
# Auto-fill template end
